    "response": "To compute the **sample standard deviation** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{25, 10, 0, 9, -1, -14, -21\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data set\n\n$$\n\\text{Mean} = \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 + (-1) + (-14) + (-21)}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 0 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7}\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{25 + 10 + 9 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7} = \\frac{34 - 1 - 14 - 21}{7} = \\frac{34 - 36}{7} = \\frac{-2}{7}\n$$\n\nSo, the **mean** is:\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = -\\frac{2}{7}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean\n\n$$\n(25 - (-\\frac{2}{7}))^2 = (25 + \\frac{2}{7})^2 = \\left(\\frac{175 + 2}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{177}{7}\\right)^2\n$$\n\n$$\n= \\frac{31329}{49}\n$$\n\n$$\n(10 - (-\\frac{2}{7}))^2 = (10 + \\frac{2}{7})^2 = \\left(\\frac{70 + 2}{7}\\right)^2 = \\left(\\frac{72}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{5184}{49}\n$$\n\n$$\n(0 - (-\\frac{2}{7}))^2 = \\left(\\frac{2}{7}\\right)^2 = \\frac{4}{49}\n$$"
